### Assistant: To find the remainder when $x^4 + x + 2$ is divided by $x - 3$, we can use polynomial long division.

First, we set up the division as follows:
\[
\begin{array}{r|lll}
x - 3 & x^4 + 0x^3 + 0x^2 + x + 2 &    \text{(Place holder for missing terms)} \\
\cline{2-4}
 & x^4 &  -3x^3 &      \text{(Divide)} \\
\cline{2-4}
 & & 3x^3 + 0x^2 &     \text{(Multiply)} \\
 & & 3x^3 &  -9x^2     \text{(Subtract)} \\
\cline{3-4}
 & & &   9x^2 + x \\
 & & &   9x^2 & -27x     \\
\cline{4-4}
 & & & & 27x + 2 \\
 & & & & 27x & -81    \\
\cline{5-5}
& & & & 83   
\end{array}
\]

Therefore, the remainder when $x^4 + x + 2$ is divided by $x - 3$ is $83$.

